"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The np.insert function is being used incorrectly in this context. The insert function does not modify the original array in place; instead, it returns a new array. The code attempts to assign the result of np.insert to arr[i], which will lead to a shape mismatch since the inserted array will have a different shape than the original row of arr.\", \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n> arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3).reshape(1, -1)\"}"